# UI implementation (Vite React app)

When editing MCP-related pages or `src/lib/mcpJsonRpc.ts`:

- Prefer the control-plane `apiClient()` for REST; use direct `fetch` JSON-RPC only for live MCP endpoints (`initialize`, `prompts/list`, etc.).
- For MCP discovery from the browser, use the same sequence as the MCP spec: `initialize`, then the desired method (`prompts/list`, etc.). Protocol version is defined in `mcpJsonRpc.ts`.
- Surface structured errors to the user (`McpRpcError`, `ApiError`).

## Reliability

- MCP HTTP calls from the SPA require **CORS** on the MCP gateway for the UI origin.
- Fail gracefully when the control plane or MCP endpoint is unreachable.

## UX

- Match existing page patterns (`card`, `data` tables, `json-block` for raw payloads).
- Keep French-friendly copy only where the product already uses it; default UI strings follow existing pages.
